01:20.618 --> 01:22.291
Go find your brother.

01:29.994 --> 01:31.871
<i>You want to make
your summer worthwhile?</i>

01:31.929 --> 01:32.999
<i>Then sign up now!</i>

01:33.064 --> 01:34.839
<i>Yay!</i>

01:37.068 --> 01:39.844
Come on, we got to go.

01:39.871 --> 01:41.714
Let go of me.
I can walk on my own.

01:44.075 --> 01:46.635
I caught him watching that commercial
for the crazy science camp.

01:46.678 --> 01:48.453
It's not a commercial.
It's an advertisement.

01:48.513 --> 01:50.691
What's the difference? Did you
at least find a bathroom?

01:50.715 --> 01:51.955
No, I got sidetracked.

01:52.016 --> 01:55.486
Albie, do you remember the last
time you tried to hold it too long?

01:55.553 --> 01:56.725
Mom, I'm fine.

02:05.530 --> 02:09.478
Hey, maybe I can go here
instead of science camp.

02:09.500 --> 02:11.537
Oh, honey, I'm sorry

02:11.602 --> 02:13.604
that science camp didn't
work out for this summer.

02:13.671 --> 02:16.050
What am I going to do with that
chemistry set that Dad gave me'?

02:16.074 --> 02:18.918
Yeah, it's really too bad that he
can't go to his dorky science camp.

02:18.976 --> 02:20.922
You know I'm committing
social suicide, right'?

02:20.978 --> 02:22.457
Hashtag life stinks.

02:22.513 --> 02:24.358
Hey, now, you guys
are going to feel differently

02:24.382 --> 02:25.542
when we get to Aunt Jackie's.

02:25.583 --> 02:26.891
Hashtag doubtful.

03:19.570 --> 03:21.811
<i>Oh, shakafaka!</i>

03:21.873 --> 03:23.875
<i>That's one for the record books,
I'll tell you.</i>

03:23.941 --> 03:25.716
<i>And we'll come back
with a lift/e more music</i>

03:25.777 --> 03:28.758
<i>after this quick
commercial break.</i>

03:28.813 --> 03:30.622
<i>Is science your life?</i>

03:30.681 --> 03:32.922
<i>If you just nodded your...</i>

03:32.984 --> 03:34.588
You belong at our camp.

03:34.652 --> 03:36.427
Oh, brother.

04:15.726 --> 04:19.765
Hi! Hey! Hey! Hi!

04:19.831 --> 04:21.902
Hey, I'm so glad to...

04:21.966 --> 04:23.104
Look at this.

04:23.167 --> 04:24.805
It's doing it on its own.

04:26.137 --> 04:28.743
Please tell me we don't have
to be seen in public with her.

04:28.806 --> 04:30.877
Oh, Tiffany, please. Cut it out.

04:30.908 --> 04:31.978
Oh, yeah.

04:32.043 --> 04:33.818
Watch this. Watch me go.

04:33.878 --> 04:36.256
Yeah! Yeah! Come on.

04:38.649 --> 04:39.889
Watch this. Oh, yeah!

04:39.951 --> 04:42.625
I can do the robot. Oh, yeah!

04:42.687 --> 04:44.530
<i>Oh, yeah! Watch!</i>

04:44.589 --> 04:46.569
Come here, come here, come here.

04:46.624 --> 04:48.160
Get over here.
Give me some sugar!

04:48.226 --> 04:50.763
Hey. No, seriously, kid.
You got any candy?

04:50.828 --> 04:52.171
You smell like Werthefis.

04:52.230 --> 04:53.800
So you're saying I'm old'?
Maybe.

04:53.865 --> 04:56.778
You know, I
used to look like her.

04:56.834 --> 04:58.836
Anyway, you are going to be
my new test subject

04:58.903 --> 05:02.180
for my comedy routine because
I can tell you are hilarious.

05:02.240 --> 05:04.720
Lookin' what-what'?

05:04.775 --> 05:05.845
Harassing him already?

05:05.910 --> 05:07.253
Of course!

05:07.512 --> 05:09.219
Hi. Good. Good ride.

05:09.280 --> 05:11.400
Thank you so much for letting
them come stay with you.

05:11.549 --> 05:13.790
Are you kidding? I'm so
excited to have them.

05:13.851 --> 05:15.262
Oh, my gosh. Are you excited?

05:15.520 --> 05:16.225
These look heavy.

05:16.287 --> 05:18.528
They're very heavy.
Okay, be careful then.

05:18.589 --> 05:19.795
Thanks.

05:19.824 --> 05:20.825
Okay, well...

05:20.892 --> 05:23.964
So Luke and I,
we got this last-minute call

05:24.028 --> 05:27.271
to go do some
seismology research in the...

05:27.532 --> 05:29.671
Blah, blah, blah. You
lost me at seismology.

05:29.700 --> 05:31.077
My niece and nephew are here.

05:31.135 --> 05:32.546
It's really exciting.

05:32.603 --> 05:35.675
They're here! They're... kids!

05:35.706 --> 05:38.186
Kids...

05:38.242 --> 05:40.085
Well, you know, they
shouldn't be much trouble.

05:40.144 --> 05:42.249
I mean, Tiffany is 16.

05:42.313 --> 05:44.691
Well, she can't be any worse
than you were at that age.

05:44.749 --> 05:48.219
What'? No. I was a great child.
Shh, shh, shh, no.

05:48.286 --> 05:50.163
Acceptance is good.

05:50.221 --> 05:51.723
<i>You were a brat.</i>

05:51.789 --> 05:53.291
Oh, come on.

05:53.558 --> 05:55.731
Which one is my room'?

05:55.793 --> 05:57.295
Tiffany, your manners.

05:58.596 --> 06:01.702
Just take whichever
room you like.

06:03.568 --> 06:05.309
Oh, she's driving me
absolutely crazy.

06:05.570 --> 06:08.107
Oh, let me tell you about Albie.

06:08.139 --> 06:09.982
Okay. Okay, he's very sensitive.

06:10.007 --> 06:11.987
Okay'? He has
a lot of allergies,

06:12.043 --> 06:14.284
so he should probably just
stay inside most of the time.

06:14.345 --> 06:16.951
Or you'll be dealing
with a lot of problems

06:17.014 --> 06:19.654
<i>like drainage and mucus.
That's a little graphic.</i>

06:19.717 --> 06:21.856
<i>Yeah. Where does
it all come from'?</i>

06:21.919 --> 06:23.921
He also has some trouble
making friends.

06:23.988 --> 06:25.160
So he likes to be alone.

06:25.222 --> 06:28.863
<i>Yeah, he can be
a little awkward.</i>

06:31.696 --> 06:33.073
He stays to himself a lot,

06:33.130 --> 06:34.200
and that's fine.

06:34.265 --> 06:37.678
Don't worry if he doesn't
really engage with you.

06:37.735 --> 06:39.737
He's Brilliant. How do you do?

06:39.770 --> 06:41.306
<i>He loves science</i>

06:41.372 --> 06:44.285
<i>and really learning
anything in a book.</i>

06:44.342 --> 06:46.151
<i>He's great.</i>

06:46.177 --> 06:49.920
Okay, I think fresh air
will do him some good.

06:49.981 --> 06:51.983
No, he should really
probably just stay inside.

06:52.049 --> 06:53.255
No, he should go outside.

06:53.317 --> 06:55.194
Yeah, you should go outside.

06:55.252 --> 06:56.925
Yep, that's it.
I'm kicking you out.

06:56.988 --> 06:58.729
Go, go. But...

06:58.789 --> 07:00.894
Tiffany? Albie'?

07:00.958 --> 07:01.958
I'm leaving.

07:02.827 --> 07:04.306
Goodbye.

07:04.362 --> 07:05.932
Bye. Bye.

07:05.997 --> 07:07.340
Be good.

07:07.398 --> 07:08.775
I'll see you
in a few weeks, okay'?

07:08.833 --> 07:10.835
Have fun.

07:12.870 --> 07:14.872
The bond between
a mother and her son,

07:14.939 --> 07:16.384
it's just, I don't know.

07:16.641 --> 07:19.349
Okay, you be good, too.

07:19.410 --> 07:22.186
Okay.

07:22.246 --> 07:23.919
Can't guarantee anything.

07:23.948 --> 07:25.825
Bye. Bye.

07:27.118 --> 07:29.257
<i>Yeah, they're safe with me.</i>

07:30.955 --> 07:32.730
Have fun in the Grenadines.

07:39.096 --> 07:41.098
Whoa, it's warm up here.

07:41.766 --> 07:44.713
<i>You've been carrying all those
books around in that bag?</i>

07:44.769 --> 07:47.272
Honey, you're going
to get a hunchback.

07:47.338 --> 07:51.753
Master, tonight is time
we bring the creation to life.

07:51.809 --> 07:53.687
Wow, looks like you've got
the tools to do it, too.

07:53.711 --> 07:55.850
This is pretty cool.

07:55.913 --> 07:59.087
There's that smile
I've been looking for.

07:59.116 --> 08:01.118
Hey, I got something
you might like.

08:03.254 --> 08:06.895
A book by Dr. Whittmore.
Did you know him'?

08:06.957 --> 08:10.097
Well, yeah, I know everyone in this town.

08:10.161 --> 08:12.767
I think a
fairy just got its wings.

08:12.830 --> 08:14.741
It's just Tiffany texting.

08:14.799 --> 08:16.107
Mmm.

08:16.167 --> 08:19.376
Apparently my friend Abella's
stepmom's uncle's new wife

08:19.403 --> 08:20.403
has a boat on the lake.

08:20.438 --> 08:22.008
And she asked me to come with.

08:22.073 --> 08:23.916
You have a friend named Abella'?

08:23.974 --> 08:25.180
Oh, I love that name.

08:25.242 --> 08:27.381
Yeah.

08:27.445 --> 08:28.788
Oh, Abella is here.

08:28.846 --> 08:31.258
Later. Oh, peace out.

08:31.315 --> 08:34.818
So what are you going to do
your first day of vacation'?

08:34.885 --> 08:36.990
This book looks informative.

08:37.020 --> 08:39.023
Did you know that
that copy is signed

08:39.090 --> 08:40.933
by Dr. Whittmore himself?

08:40.991 --> 08:43.870
He gave it to our family
along, longtime ago.

08:43.928 --> 08:46.772
But can't let you
read it just yet.

08:47.865 --> 08:48.434
Why not'?

08:48.499 --> 08:50.035
We have to rehearse.

08:50.101 --> 08:51.136
Huh?

08:51.168 --> 08:53.148
Yeah.

08:53.204 --> 08:54.740
We have an audition
in 20 minutes.

09:00.745 --> 09:04.488
<i>♪ I once was lost ♪</i>

09:04.749 --> 09:07.229
♪ But now I'm found ♪

09:07.284 --> 09:13.030
♪ Was blind but now I see ♪

09:23.868 --> 09:27.008
Um, bril...

09:27.071 --> 09:29.210
Deligh...

09:29.273 --> 09:31.116
Exes...

09:31.175 --> 09:32.779
Satis...

09:32.810 --> 09:34.949
Amazing.

09:35.012 --> 09:35.888
Did you write that'?

09:35.946 --> 09:38.392
No. Oh.

09:38.449 --> 09:42.329
"Many mumbling mice"

09:42.386 --> 09:46.163
"are making merry music
in the moonlight."

09:46.223 --> 09:47.463
You're on in 10, Mr. Savage.

09:47.525 --> 09:48.833
Thank you, Ted.

09:48.893 --> 09:50.201
It's Cheryl.

09:50.261 --> 09:52.070
Really? Mm-hmm.

09:52.096 --> 09:54.804
Oh.

09:54.865 --> 09:57.937
Next up, Eday Savage.

09:57.968 --> 09:59.003
Oh, French.

09:59.069 --> 10:00.480
Eddie Savage.

10:00.538 --> 10:01.539
Eddie Savage?

10:01.806 --> 10:02.876
That's not French at all.

10:05.843 --> 10:08.414
Hi.

10:08.479 --> 10:11.016
Ladies and gentlemen of Culver,

10:11.081 --> 10:13.527
I will now magically
right before your eyes

10:13.584 --> 10:16.997
bake a cake.

10:25.396 --> 10:27.239
Well, that's disgusting.

10:38.976 --> 10:41.388
Oh, that's... that had
better be gluten-free.

10:59.129 --> 11:00.870
Now...

11:02.867 --> 11:04.869
Ladies and gentlemen... No.

11:04.935 --> 11:06.175
Luive you...

11:06.237 --> 11:07.409
No, no, don't.

11:07.471 --> 11:09.144
Cake!

11:11.876 --> 11:13.549
Why would you even?

11:17.181 --> 11:18.285
Ta-da!

11:21.285 --> 11:23.026
Next!

11:23.053 --> 11:24.333
You might want to clean that up.

11:24.388 --> 11:26.148
Okay, so first thing
we got to do is sign in,

11:26.190 --> 11:28.192
and then were going
to scope out the competition.

11:28.259 --> 11:30.170
Hello there,

11:30.227 --> 11:31.968
ventriloquist boy.

11:32.029 --> 11:34.236
Oh, yes. What is he, like six'?

11:34.298 --> 11:36.039
Dude, we got this.

11:37.534 --> 11:39.309
<i>Wow, look at her.</i>

11:39.370 --> 11:43.045
In her little baton
twirling, sequined dress.

11:44.575 --> 11:46.179
That's our competition.

11:54.051 --> 11:56.361
What the frick
is going on, Garrison?

11:56.420 --> 11:58.058
<i>It's a summer competition.</i>

11:58.088 --> 12:00.295
It's the auditions.
Oh, one time,

12:00.357 --> 12:01.995
I was at a Denny's
with my family.

12:02.059 --> 12:03.970
We just got up in the
middle of the restaurant,

12:04.028 --> 12:05.507
started singing
the national anthem.

12:05.562 --> 12:07.564
It was Presidents' Day.
I was feeling patriotic.

12:07.631 --> 12:10.134
And when I was done,
standing ovation.

12:10.200 --> 12:11.338
Nice. Yeah.

12:13.671 --> 12:16.345
You know, I'm thinking about
going into the talent show.

12:16.407 --> 12:18.318
Check this out. What
would your talent be'?

12:19.710 --> 12:21.451
Hey.

12:21.512 --> 12:23.549
Hey, your ball'?
Your ball went in there'?

12:23.614 --> 12:26.220
Oh, let's see. Oh, right there.

12:26.283 --> 12:27.626
Boo!

12:33.624 --> 12:35.399
Right'? Right'?

12:35.459 --> 12:37.496
<i>Oh, I get it. Whoo!</i>

12:37.528 --> 12:38.632
I get it. I get it.

12:38.696 --> 12:42.303
You'd be going as a ghost
who stuffs kids in trash cans.

12:45.336 --> 12:46.644
What'?

12:51.976 --> 12:54.252
Okay. Sorry I ruined it.

12:54.311 --> 12:56.188
What are you talking about'?

12:56.246 --> 12:59.022
That was... That was hilarious.

12:59.083 --> 13:01.120
It was, you know...
We were okay.

13:01.185 --> 13:02.721
Hey, I got to go
to the grocery store.

13:02.987 --> 13:04.591
So you want to hang here

13:04.655 --> 13:06.532
and you know,
meet me by the boat

13:06.590 --> 13:08.126
in say, half an hour?

13:08.592 --> 13:11.163
I don't know.
What don't you know?

13:11.228 --> 13:13.006
You got to get out there.
You got to make friends.

13:13.030 --> 13:14.509
You got to be a man about town.

13:14.565 --> 13:16.676
Hey, if you see Tiffany you
tell her to meet me by the boat

13:16.700 --> 13:18.543
by five o'clock, okay'?
No later.

13:18.602 --> 13:21.014
Five o'clock. Have fun.

13:26.243 --> 13:29.281
Yeah, I know, right'?

13:29.313 --> 13:31.088
Oh, man. Oh!

13:31.148 --> 13:33.355
So you here for the whole summer?
I don't know.

13:33.417 --> 13:35.462
Yeah, my dad won't tell me
why we came back out here.

13:35.486 --> 13:37.193
I remember when
you used to live here.

13:37.254 --> 13:38.255
You were tiny.

13:38.322 --> 13:40.233
That's 'cause I was six.

13:51.802 --> 13:53.372
Huh, look what we have here.

13:53.437 --> 13:55.110
A little... Dweeb.

13:55.172 --> 13:56.742
No one says "dweeb" anymore.

13:56.807 --> 13:58.582
What are you doing here, dweeb'?

13:58.642 --> 14:00.644
Technically, I'm more
of a bookworm.

14:00.711 --> 14:02.281
"Dweeb" is vintage, all right'?

14:02.346 --> 14:03.484
It's totally in.

14:03.547 --> 14:05.254
Your mom is vintage.
Okay, shut up.

14:05.315 --> 14:06.817
No one plays your mom anymore.

14:07.084 --> 14:08.328
Come on, I asked you a question.

14:08.352 --> 14:09.352
What are you doing here?

14:09.386 --> 14:10.626
I was auditioning.

14:10.687 --> 14:12.724
He's auditioning.

14:12.790 --> 14:14.736
I know what he
was auditioning for.

14:14.758 --> 14:17.170
He was auditioning
for a-a-a dweeb!

14:21.799 --> 14:23.472
What...

14:25.836 --> 14:27.372
A science book?

14:27.438 --> 14:29.645
This kid's got a science book
in the middle of summer.

14:29.706 --> 14:32.346
I mean, how much of a loser
do you got to be'?

14:32.409 --> 14:34.389
You know, this kid from the...

14:34.445 --> 14:35.856
You know what I'm saying?

14:36.113 --> 14:38.115
Right'? Right'? Whoa!

14:39.650 --> 14:40.720
Oh, you didn't.

14:40.784 --> 14:44.231
If you do not leave him be,
I will cast a spell on you

14:44.288 --> 14:45.494
<i>that will tum you purple</i>

14:45.556 --> 14:47.092
<i>and then green</i>

14:47.157 --> 14:49.103
and I will put hair on your back

14:49.159 --> 14:51.161
<i>and boils on your face.</i>

14:51.228 --> 14:54.437
An evil mutant plague shall be cast
upon you and your entire family.

14:54.498 --> 14:56.102
I'm not touching him.

14:59.303 --> 15:01.806
Is this how you saw this going?

15:01.872 --> 15:04.614
No. Can I admit something?

15:04.675 --> 15:06.245
If you must.

15:06.310 --> 15:08.415
I don't really know magic.

15:08.479 --> 15:09.787
Good to know.

15:11.882 --> 15:13.452
<i>Whoa!</i>

15:22.893 --> 15:24.770
What's up, Aaron?

15:24.828 --> 15:26.637
The lake is pretty clean.

15:31.835 --> 15:33.473
I love summer.

15:33.537 --> 15:34.607
I hate it.

15:34.671 --> 15:36.548
I just want to leave.

15:36.607 --> 15:38.553
Hey, there are two things
you should know.

15:38.575 --> 15:40.782
Number one, never let
anyone see you cry in public.

15:40.844 --> 15:42.414
And the second thing'?

15:42.479 --> 15:45.289
Well, look at the bright side.

15:45.349 --> 15:47.295
Now we get to have our revenge.

15:47.351 --> 15:48.561
And how are we
going to do that'?

15:48.585 --> 15:50.462
Well, my cousins, the Savages.

15:50.521 --> 15:51.864
Who?

15:51.922 --> 15:53.833
They live
on the outskirts of town

15:53.857 --> 15:55.495
beyond the junkyard.

15:55.559 --> 15:58.438
Some say they
were born of Vikings,

15:58.495 --> 16:01.169
raised by wolves
and trained samurai...

16:01.231 --> 16:02.369
Can I stop you right there'?

16:02.432 --> 16:04.878
Samurai haven't
been around since 1871.

16:04.935 --> 16:06.846
Oh, did I say samurai?

16:06.870 --> 16:09.248
I meant covert ninjas.

16:09.306 --> 16:10.546
Ch-ch-ch-ch-chow!

16:10.607 --> 16:13.554
I'll pass. I just want
to be left alone.

16:16.446 --> 16:20.292
We shall be avenged!

16:21.818 --> 16:23.525
He's not on Facebook.

16:23.587 --> 16:24.895
Are you for reals'? I know.

16:24.955 --> 16:26.457
I was like, "I can't believe"

16:26.523 --> 16:27.866
"you don't have the Internet."

16:27.925 --> 16:29.199
And he says,

16:29.259 --> 16:30.533
"I have the Internet."

16:30.594 --> 16:31.834
"I just don't have Facebook."

16:31.895 --> 16:34.398
I'm confused.
It doesn't make sense.

16:34.464 --> 16:36.809
How am I ever supposed to figure
out his relationship status'?

16:36.833 --> 16:39.871
That's what I'm saying.
Excuse me.

16:39.937 --> 16:41.211
Oh, my aunt is here.

16:41.238 --> 16:42.376
Great. Later.

16:42.439 --> 16:43.543
Bye. Bye.

16:46.843 --> 16:48.754
Do you two not own a watch'?

16:48.779 --> 16:50.918
Huh'? Seriously,
you're like 20 minutes late.

16:50.981 --> 16:54.758
Uh, no. Only old
people wear watches.

16:54.785 --> 16:56.230
Oops.

16:56.253 --> 16:57.755
Oh. Oh, Well...

16:57.821 --> 16:59.300
lucky for me

16:59.356 --> 17:01.632
I don't own a watch.

17:01.692 --> 17:03.000
Oops.

17:03.260 --> 17:04.500
Aunt Jackie, Abella just wrote.

17:04.560 --> 17:05.681
Can I have dinner with her'?

17:05.729 --> 17:07.299
Yeah, yeah.

17:07.364 --> 17:09.901
Please, go have dinner with her.

17:09.967 --> 17:11.640
Thanks, bye. Bye.

17:13.637 --> 17:16.810
I'll miss you.

17:16.873 --> 17:19.819
So it looks like it's just
me and you for dinner.

17:19.876 --> 17:20.980
What you say, Albie'?

17:21.244 --> 17:23.452
Sure. Sure, okay.

17:23.512 --> 17:26.824
Hey, I see finally decided
to go for a swim.

17:26.883 --> 17:28.988
Proud of you.

17:29.253 --> 17:30.323
It wasn't by choice.

17:30.387 --> 17:32.958
Oh, well then I take it back.

17:33.023 --> 17:34.400
Clutz.

17:45.502 --> 17:47.482
<i>Well-known philanthropist.</i>

17:47.537 --> 17:50.279
<i>We all knew Mr. Whittmore
was a bit of an eccentric.</i>

17:50.340 --> 17:51.717
<i>He once said in an interview</i>

17:51.775 --> 17:53.948
<i>that he never really fit in.</i>

17:54.011 --> 17:56.287
<i>Interesting news
in regards to his will</i>

17:56.346 --> 17:59.293
<i>is surfacing now,
a year after his passing.</i>

17:59.316 --> 18:00.386
<i>Thank you, Daisy.</i>

18:00.450 --> 18:02.487
<i>We'll have more
as that story develops.</i>

18:02.552 --> 18:04.293
Why do you think it took so long

18:04.354 --> 18:06.425
to release Mr. Whittmore's
final statement?

18:06.490 --> 18:08.697
I don't know the logistics
behind it all,

18:08.759 --> 18:11.797
but the news that Mr. Whittmore
has hidden a treasure chest

18:11.862 --> 18:13.842
containing a sizable amount
of his estate

18:13.897 --> 18:15.433
has officially been released.

18:15.499 --> 18:16.910
Do you think it was a final ploy

18:16.967 --> 18:19.538
to increase tourism in this
town he loved and called home?

18:19.603 --> 18:22.482
Culver doesn't need any more
tourists during the summer.

18:22.539 --> 18:23.483
We do fine already.

18:23.540 --> 18:26.885
But it is buried here in Culver.
Yes.

18:26.943 --> 18:28.479
And Mr. Whittmore hid clues

18:28.545 --> 18:30.456
to help one
lucky individual find it'?

18:30.514 --> 18:32.016
That's right.

18:32.082 --> 18:34.653
Well, I think we can expect
our little town

18:34.718 --> 18:36.925
to get a bit busier
over the next few days.

18:36.987 --> 18:38.330
I'm Daisy Larson,

18:38.355 --> 18:39.698
Channel 11 News.

18:40.824 --> 18:43.600
Now, Mr. Whittmore was known
for being an inventor,

18:43.660 --> 18:46.368
but he was actually a very
accomplished businessman.

18:46.430 --> 18:48.671
In fact, he gave loans
to other businessmen

18:48.732 --> 18:50.678
hoping to better the community.

18:50.734 --> 18:53.476
Have you ever been
to Whittmore's root beer stand'?

18:53.537 --> 18:55.039
No. No'?

18:55.105 --> 18:56.880
Well, Mr. Whittmore

18:56.907 --> 18:58.750
gave a man named Fritz Bronson

18:58.809 --> 19:01.756
a sizable loan
to start the root beer stand.

19:01.812 --> 19:03.018
With your contributions

19:03.080 --> 19:04.787
I'd like to open
a root beer stand

19:04.848 --> 19:08.887
where patrons can enjoy a nice
cold beverage during the summer.

19:08.919 --> 19:12.662
That sounds like the best
idea I've ever heard.

19:12.723 --> 19:15.067
<i>He just loved the idea
of seeing the community flourish.</i>

19:15.125 --> 19:17.537
He wanted that to be his legacy.

19:31.041 --> 19:34.614
All right.

19:34.678 --> 19:36.658
The root beer stand
was very popular.

19:36.713 --> 19:39.091
But Fritz was always looking
for a way to make more money.

19:39.149 --> 19:42.596
So he wanted to sell the root
beer stand to turn a profit.

19:42.652 --> 19:45.531
But Dr. Whittmore didn't want
something that the community enjoyed

19:45.555 --> 19:47.466
to go away,

19:47.524 --> 19:49.595
so he bought it from Fritz.

19:49.659 --> 19:51.536
I've never had root beer.

19:51.561 --> 19:53.666
You've never had root beer.

19:53.697 --> 19:55.768
Okay, I don't even know
what to say to that.

19:55.832 --> 19:56.936
I'm going to take you.

19:57.000 --> 19:58.570
I think I'm allergic.

19:58.635 --> 20:01.912
Maybe you will meet some new
friends and they can take you.

20:02.906 --> 20:04.886
I don't think people
like me here.

20:04.941 --> 20:06.943
Why would you say that'?

20:06.977 --> 20:10.618
This boy kind of threw me
in the lake.

20:19.423 --> 20:20.902
That's the guy.

20:22.659 --> 20:24.969
<i>Oh, Billy Bronson.</i>

20:36.173 --> 20:39.017
It's pretty late. Sorry,
I lost track of time.

20:39.075 --> 20:41.475
I don't think you should be
hanging out with kids like Billy.

20:41.511 --> 20:44.082
Okay. Tiffany, if you don't learn
to function without that thing,

20:44.147 --> 20:45.785
your brain is going
to turn into mush.

20:45.849 --> 20:47.795
Tiffany. Yeah.

20:47.851 --> 20:49.429
Why would you want
to hang outwith people

20:49.453 --> 20:51.956
who think it's cool to throw
kids in the lake'? Jackie!

20:52.022 --> 20:53.899
You whiny little tattletale.

20:53.957 --> 20:55.201
<i>Billy just said
they were having fun.</i>

20:55.225 --> 20:56.636
That is your brother.

20:56.693 --> 20:58.570
Just leave me alone, okay'?

20:58.628 --> 20:59.971
I don't even want to be here.

21:00.030 --> 21:02.738
You know, just because
Mom and Dad are too busy for us

21:02.799 --> 21:03.943
doesn't mean they
just dump us here.

21:03.967 --> 21:06.072
Okay, that's unfair.
Life is unfair.

21:12.676 --> 21:14.121
They're not too busy.

21:18.114 --> 21:20.185
Maybe we all
just need some sleep.

21:20.250 --> 21:21.888
<i>Come on.</i>

21:43.807 --> 21:44.717
Get dressed.

21:44.774 --> 21:47.050
Grandma needs an oil change.

21:47.110 --> 21:48.589
My pontoon boat,

21:48.645 --> 21:49.919
I named her Grandma

21:49.946 --> 21:51.118
after my grandma.

21:51.181 --> 21:52.592
She needs an oil change.

21:52.649 --> 21:53.787
Get dressed.

22:14.738 --> 22:16.149
Yeah. What was I
telling you, man'?

22:16.206 --> 22:19.551
They just ran off.
It was so great.

22:19.576 --> 22:22.819
And I was like,
that's not his hand.

22:22.879 --> 22:25.086
<i>Walk away. Walk away.</i>

22:25.148 --> 22:27.560
<i>I was like, whoa.</i>

22:27.584 --> 22:28.824
Oh, man.

22:28.885 --> 22:30.592
I need you to tune this up.

22:30.654 --> 22:31.864
Yeah, I need it in tip top shape

22:31.888 --> 22:33.993
for this weekend's
Wave Runner competition.

22:34.057 --> 22:35.737
Yeah, we've got a heavy
workload this week,

22:35.792 --> 22:37.003
but I can take
a look at it for you.

22:37.027 --> 22:38.904
Well, you take
a look at it then.

22:38.962 --> 22:40.635
In the meantime,
we'll be out there

22:40.697 --> 22:42.233
smashing it up
in my new Master craft.

22:42.265 --> 22:44.040
Oh, yeah, the green one,
number 25.

22:44.100 --> 22:45.602
It's the green one behind you.

22:45.669 --> 22:46.670
It's so fast.

22:46.736 --> 22:47.736
Yeah, it's nice.

22:47.771 --> 22:48.909
How fast is it, Harley?

22:48.972 --> 22:52.181
It's like a cheetah
on a treadmill. Just...

22:54.244 --> 22:56.190
Oh, I totally know.

22:56.246 --> 22:57.919
Well, let me incline real quick.

22:57.981 --> 22:59.221
You know?

22:59.282 --> 23:02.263
It's like that, bro.
It's like that, bro.

23:05.088 --> 23:06.863
That makes no sense.

23:06.890 --> 23:09.734
What was that'?

23:09.759 --> 23:11.033
<i>He said something.</i>

23:11.094 --> 23:12.732
Are you challenging me, bro'?

23:12.762 --> 23:14.901
Because I see you
in your competition

23:14.965 --> 23:18.071
coming in third, fourth.

23:18.134 --> 23:20.646
I had a messed up ankle, but I could
take you any day of the week.

23:20.670 --> 23:22.274
<i>Oh-ho! Did you hear that?</i>

23:22.339 --> 23:23.977
Any day of the week.

23:24.040 --> 23:25.781
<i>Okay, we can
go out there right now.</i>

23:25.842 --> 23:27.617
Yeah? Yeah.

23:27.677 --> 23:29.156
Yeah? Go ahead.

23:32.782 --> 23:33.920
I can't. I'm working.

23:33.984 --> 23:35.964
You can't because
you know you'd lose.

23:42.726 --> 23:43.636
That's a crow.

23:43.693 --> 23:45.695
It's a chicken-crow, bro.

23:48.231 --> 23:50.677
Billy, anytime after hours.

23:50.734 --> 23:53.305
Yeah, well, after you
tune up my Wave Runner.

23:55.372 --> 23:59.184
Yeah.

23:59.242 --> 24:01.017
I was going to get the yellow.

24:01.077 --> 24:02.920
You were going to get it yellow?
Yeah, yellow.

24:02.979 --> 24:04.287
I like green, Billy. Yeah.

24:04.347 --> 24:06.054
You always make good decisions.

24:08.685 --> 24:10.096
I'll be here about 30 minutes

24:10.153 --> 24:13.999
so why don't you go outside and play'?

24:14.057 --> 24:15.730
Do you even know
what "go play" means?

24:15.792 --> 24:17.362
It means get out of here.
Go be a kid.

24:17.427 --> 24:18.735
Go.

24:43.687 --> 24:45.360
Here it is.

24:45.422 --> 24:47.368
Oh, okay.

24:47.390 --> 24:49.097
It fell off.

24:50.427 --> 24:52.703
Shazam.

24:52.762 --> 24:53.762
Yes!

24:54.898 --> 24:55.968
Oh.

24:56.032 --> 24:58.740
No, I didn't like it.

24:59.969 --> 25:01.107
Okay.

25:01.137 --> 25:02.377
You know, but I mean,

25:02.439 --> 25:03.918
you put in some effort.

25:03.973 --> 25:06.146
So. Well, there's that.

25:06.209 --> 25:07.984
Extra point. That's something.

25:10.113 --> 25:12.423
Trespasser! Let's get him!

25:12.482 --> 25:14.189
Hey, hey, hey. It's okay.

25:14.250 --> 25:15.991
I know him.

25:16.052 --> 25:17.395
Let him prove himself.

25:19.155 --> 25:21.157
So you do any tricks'?

25:21.224 --> 25:24.034
I don't have a bike
like you guys.

25:24.094 --> 25:25.732
He doesn't have a bike.

25:25.795 --> 25:29.140
Eddie, get him
Old Man Kettle's bike.

25:29.199 --> 25:31.338
Oh.

25:31.401 --> 25:32.880
Not sure if he could handle.

25:32.936 --> 25:35.280
Old Man Kettle's bike.

25:35.338 --> 25:38.785
Wait, is this the kid that cried
when he got tossed in the lake?

25:38.842 --> 25:39.912
That's him.

25:39.976 --> 25:41.284
<i>Oh, where are my manners?</i>

25:41.344 --> 25:43.950
Albie, this is Winnie

25:44.013 --> 25:45.754
and Vinny. Hi.

25:45.815 --> 25:48.022
They're my cousins.

25:48.084 --> 25:50.223
Who was Old Man Kettle'?

25:50.286 --> 25:52.960
He's Culver's only homeless person.
Yeah.

25:53.022 --> 25:55.195
<i>He ditched his bike
on the side of the road</i>

25:55.258 --> 25:56.828
before he disappeared.

25:56.893 --> 25:58.429
Guess who found the bike.

25:58.495 --> 25:59.940
Him?

25:59.996 --> 26:01.066
Mm-mm.

26:01.131 --> 26:03.168
I did.

26:03.233 --> 26:04.233
She did. He did.

26:05.502 --> 26:07.038
We did.

26:07.103 --> 26:08.514
Sometimes I see her thoughts.

26:08.772 --> 26:10.774
Yeah, and sometimes it's creepy.

26:10.807 --> 26:12.809
Old Man Kettle
didn't have any teeth.

26:12.876 --> 26:15.356
Legend has it he lost them

26:15.411 --> 26:16.411
riding his bike.

26:17.480 --> 26:19.482
She's a tough ride.

26:19.549 --> 26:21.256
Why don't you go get it for him'?
Yeah.

26:21.317 --> 26:23.991
Oh, yeah.

26:24.053 --> 26:27.262
I've always wondered why he keeps
wearing that top hat and cape.

26:27.323 --> 26:28.996
He goes through phases.

26:29.058 --> 26:32.198
Yeah, last month, he thought he was
a professional baseball player.

26:32.262 --> 26:33.969
Now he thinks he's a magician.

26:34.030 --> 26:37.102
And next month, he's probably going
to think he's a sumo wrestler.

26:42.972 --> 26:44.918
Well, if you're up for a race,

26:44.974 --> 26:46.851
<i>I'm sure Old Man Kettle
wouldn't mind</i>

26:46.910 --> 26:49.015
you borrowing his bike.

26:49.078 --> 26:51.991
And I was a professional
baseball player.

26:52.048 --> 26:53.925
Um, I don't think
I'm going to ride that.

26:53.983 --> 26:55.519
If you want to hang
with the Savages,

26:55.585 --> 26:56.928
you kind of have to race us.

26:56.986 --> 26:59.296
Are you here to bike
or be a sissy?

26:59.355 --> 27:00.834
No.

27:00.890 --> 27:02.563
Hey, you allergic
to bikes, too'?

27:05.028 --> 27:06.439
<i>There you go.</i>

27:06.496 --> 27:08.498
<i>Come on, race Winnie.</i>

27:08.565 --> 27:10.010
She's a girl.

27:10.066 --> 27:12.512
Hey. That's debatable.

27:12.569 --> 27:14.515
Yeah. All right, I'll do it.

27:14.571 --> 27:16.107
That a boy.

27:16.139 --> 27:17.914
All right, so...

27:17.974 --> 27:20.113
down the hill,
through the dirt track,

27:20.176 --> 27:21.553
and hang a left
at the graveyard.

27:21.611 --> 27:22.988
First person back wins.

27:23.046 --> 27:23.581
I got this.

27:23.847 --> 27:25.884
Did he say graveyard?

27:25.949 --> 27:27.326
Dead people live there.

27:27.383 --> 27:29.920
Woo... Ready...

27:29.986 --> 27:31.988
set... go!

27:34.290 --> 27:35.530
Let's go.

27:36.993 --> 27:38.597
<i>I bet 20 bucks on Winnie.</i>

28:07.156 --> 28:09.158
He's like an expert on that.

28:25.208 --> 28:26.278
Ah!

28:26.342 --> 28:27.446
Oh!

28:27.510 --> 28:28.511
My'

28:33.082 --> 28:35.221
You okay?

28:35.285 --> 28:37.196
Old Man Kettle's bike is a hog.

28:37.253 --> 28:38.493
You were flying.

28:38.554 --> 28:40.329
Did that hurt'?

28:40.356 --> 28:41.699
It was amazing.

28:41.958 --> 28:43.494
Albie is a champ.

28:43.559 --> 28:45.664
I want a rematch.

28:45.929 --> 28:47.135
You could have won.

28:47.196 --> 28:48.231
I know.

28:49.933 --> 28:51.344
Welcome to the Savages.

28:53.636 --> 28:55.206
You okay'? I'm good.

28:57.073 --> 29:01.021
All righty, so we changed
the oil on the pontoon.

29:01.077 --> 29:03.683
Okay. And we did a routine
maintenance check.

29:03.947 --> 29:05.688
And it turns out it had bad gas.

29:05.949 --> 29:08.088
Oh, poor Grandma.

29:08.151 --> 29:09.494
That happens when you get older.

29:09.519 --> 29:12.295
Ba-dam-bam! Hmm?

29:15.325 --> 29:16.998
Hey, how much do I owe you'?

29:17.060 --> 29:19.131
I already fixed you.
You're good to go.

29:19.195 --> 29:21.436
No extra charge? No,
consider it on the house.

29:21.497 --> 29:23.534
Todd, you're the best.
Thank you.

29:23.599 --> 29:25.169
Of course. Hello.

29:25.234 --> 29:27.111
Hey, Todd. Winnie fell
off her bike.

29:27.170 --> 29:30.049
Oh, Oh. I didn't fall. I flew.

29:30.106 --> 29:31.449
All right, thank you.

29:31.507 --> 29:32.718
Here, let me help you with that.

29:32.742 --> 29:34.415
Here, let's see it.

29:36.179 --> 29:37.317
Are you a nurse?

29:37.380 --> 29:39.553
No, no.

29:39.615 --> 29:41.117
I'm more of a comedian.

29:41.184 --> 29:43.528
Oh. OW.

29:43.553 --> 29:45.055
You know what'?

29:45.121 --> 29:47.366
That looks bad. I don't think
this is going to do the trick.

29:47.390 --> 29:48.232
I'll tell you what.

29:48.324 --> 29:50.702
Why don't you all
come back to my house,

29:50.760 --> 29:52.706
and I can clean up your knee

29:52.762 --> 29:55.402
and I can feed you all dinner.

29:55.465 --> 29:57.411
Truth is, I make a mean lasagna.

29:57.433 --> 29:59.071
Score!

29:59.135 --> 30:01.445
I love people who feed me.

30:01.504 --> 30:03.313
Thank you.

30:21.190 --> 30:22.760
Hey. Good morning.

30:23.026 --> 30:25.700
Could you tell Billy
to come in for appetizers?

30:25.762 --> 30:27.571
Where is he'?

30:27.597 --> 30:29.599
Outback.

30:29.665 --> 30:32.441
Aw, geez.

30:43.646 --> 30:46.559
Billy!

30:46.616 --> 30:47.526
What are you doing?

30:47.583 --> 30:50.063
What is that, yoga'?

30:50.086 --> 30:51.588
Dinner! Let's go!

30:51.654 --> 30:53.634
Oh, here I come, Dad.

30:53.689 --> 30:55.430
I'll be right there.

31:00.263 --> 31:02.607
Dinner already?

31:02.632 --> 31:04.509
I've only done
five turnarounds, Dad.

31:04.567 --> 31:07.343
What's the kid doing?
He's out there like this.

31:07.403 --> 31:09.474
He looks like... who rides
a jet ski on their back'?

31:09.539 --> 31:10.813
It's summer.

31:11.074 --> 31:12.348
It's what they do.

31:12.375 --> 31:14.480
Like a repulsive seal.

31:14.544 --> 31:15.818
What are you doing?

31:16.079 --> 31:17.422
It's cheese time, Mr. Fritz.

31:17.480 --> 31:18.550
Oh, it is cheese time'?

31:18.614 --> 31:23.359
It's cheese time. Can
you make a quesadilla'?

31:23.419 --> 31:25.262
Yes. Okay, go do it.

31:25.321 --> 31:27.301
<i>So I met with the mayor today.</i>

31:27.356 --> 31:29.768
Did you'? Mm-hmm, and I'm finally
going to be able to prove

31:29.826 --> 31:33.137
once and for all that that
root beer stand is mine.

31:33.196 --> 31:36.871
Why'? Why can't we
just go back to Chicago?

31:37.133 --> 31:39.636
Billy, use your dome, okay'?

31:39.702 --> 31:42.808
The Whittmore treasure hunt
is about to begin any day now.

31:42.872 --> 31:45.546
And I know that he hid
a clue in that root beer stand.

31:45.608 --> 31:46.882
He did love that thing.

31:47.143 --> 31:49.646
Who likes root beer'? You
drink root beer'? Yeah.

31:49.712 --> 31:51.248
You do. Mm-hmm.

31:51.314 --> 31:52.486
Who else drinks root beer'?

31:52.548 --> 31:53.788
<i>Every-everyone, really.</i>

31:53.850 --> 31:56.524
The community absolutely
loves it there, Fritz.

31:58.554 --> 31:59.658
They love it.

32:01.157 --> 32:02.597
Here's what
we're going to do, okay'?

32:02.625 --> 32:04.385
Okay. You and your friends
are going to start

32:04.427 --> 32:05.747
digging around there, okay'?
Okay.

32:05.795 --> 32:07.468
Once the first clue is released.

32:07.530 --> 32:09.339
We'll just make it look
like you found it.

32:09.398 --> 32:13.210
Wait, so that means you
know where the treasure is'?

32:13.269 --> 32:14.577
Do I know where
the treasure is'?

32:14.637 --> 32:16.275
Yeah, do you know where it is'?

32:16.339 --> 32:18.546
No. Where? It's buried.

32:18.574 --> 32:20.144
Guess where it's buried. Where?

32:20.176 --> 32:22.713
Deep in a seashell in the ocean.

32:22.778 --> 32:24.815
And there's a big man
with a gray beard

32:24.881 --> 32:26.554
<i>named Neptune,
and he's holding it.</i>

32:26.582 --> 32:28.289
<i>Isn't that exciting?</i>

32:28.317 --> 32:29.895
Billy, grow up.
You believe in unicorns'?

32:29.919 --> 32:31.830
I don't know where it is!

32:31.888 --> 32:34.630
What are you, five?

32:34.690 --> 32:36.567
How much sun did you get today'?

32:37.727 --> 32:40.708
Uh, I don't know.

32:40.730 --> 32:43.301
You're wearing
lime green shorts.

32:43.366 --> 32:44.709
When you wear lime shorts,

32:44.767 --> 32:46.474
what do you look like?

32:46.536 --> 32:49.710
What did I tell you'?

32:49.739 --> 32:51.912
Sn-snowcone.

32:52.175 --> 32:53.449
You look like a snow cone.

32:53.509 --> 32:56.615
What are you doing? You want
to be a human snow cone?

32:56.679 --> 32:58.181
Now, why do you
have to do that'?

32:58.247 --> 32:59.487
I don't want to be a snow cone.

32:59.549 --> 33:00.926
